bodyEn:
To: The Beneficiary (name unknown; identified by VPA {VPA_PAYEE})
Account {BENEFICIARY_ACCOUNT_NO} (IFSC {BENEFICIARY_IFSC})
{BENEFICIARY_BANK}

Subject: Friendly request — refund of wrong UPI transfer Rs. {AMOUNT} (UTR {UTR}, {TXN_DATE}) from VPA {VPA}

Madam / Sir,

1. I, {USER_NAME}, am writing this friendly letter to request your cooperation in restoring an amount that was wrongly credited to your account by me on {TXN_DATE} (UTR {UTR}): Rs. {AMOUNT} was sent to VPA {VPA_PAYEE} (Account {BENEFICIARY_ACCOUNT_NO}, IFSC {BENEFICIARY_IFSC}).

2. On {TXN_DATE}, at around __:__ hours, while using my UPI app for a payment to my landlord (VPA {VPA}), I accidentally selected an adjacent contact — your VPA — and confirmed. The amount was credited to you within seconds.

3. Although the RBI has reserved the formal Wrong-Transfer Dispute Redressal Mechanism (DRM) for last resort, I hope to settle this amicably in order to avoid escalating to your bank {BENEFICIARY_BANK}. Please find below a copy of the UPI transaction slip establishing receipt.

4. I therefore request:
   (a) Refund the full Rs. {AMOUNT} via the originating UPI transaction (a reverse-credit from your app back to mine) within 48 hours;
   (b) Confirmation by email / SMS to my mobile {MOBILE_NO}.

5. Should you fail to respond or refuse, my next course of action will be DRM through {BENEFICIARY_BANK} (free of cost to you, but the bank will debit your account and credit me) and, in the alternative, a Cyber Cell complaint under Section 403 IPC for dishonest retention of money. I would prefer not to.

I thank you in anticipation of your fair cooperation, and remain willing to consider any mutually-acceptable settlement.

Place: {PLACE}
Date: {TODAY_DATE}

Yours sincerely,
{USER_NAME}
